1. Upload a file into HDFS. Count number of occurrences of each word in the file.
   - create a text file in local machine.
     ```
     Red green blue
     red Red green
     BLUE Green black
     red green blue
     ```
   - create a folder in hdfs and upload the file there (using hadoop fs -put ...).
   - create external table with single column and the hdfs folder location.
   
   create external table word_data(
  word STRING
  )
  location '/user/prathamesh/wordcount/input'

   
   - lower case line, split by space, then explode array.
   - group by word and count.


SELECT 
    word_out AS words, 
    COUNT(1) AS count 
FROM word_data
LATERAL VIEW explode(split(lower(word), ' ')) worddata AS word_out
GROUP BY word_out;


